| Risk | Likelihood | Impact |
|---|---|---|
| Exposed `sk_live_` key already scraped from git history | High | Critical — immediate financial fraud |
| Unauthenticated actor triggering mass charges | High | Critical — PCI-DSS breach, financial liability |
| Negative `amount` value exploited for refunds | Medium | High |
| Unhandled async rejection crashing Node process | Medium | High — full service outage |
| Client-supplied key used for account enumeration | Medium | High |

