## [EDGE CASES & RISKS]

| Risk | Severity | Mitigation Applied |
|---|---|---|
| **XSS → localStorage token theft** | 🔴 High | CSP headers + HttpOnly cookies are the real fix; `localStorage` is inherently XSS-vulnerable. For high-security apps, move to `HttpOnly` cookie-based sessions. |
| **Client-side JWT "verification"** | 🔴 High | Explicitly noted in code comments — `decodeTokenPayload` is NOT cryptographic verification. All sensitive operations must re-verify the token server-side. |
| **Token not invalidated on logout** | 🟠 Medium | `logout()` has a comment prompting a `/auth/logout` API call; JWTs are stateless by default, so server-side blocklisting or short expiry is required. |
| **Storage quota exceeded** | 🟡 Low | `storage.get/set/clear` are wrapped in try/catch; failure is non-fatal. |
| **`atob` not available in all environments** | 🟡 Low | `atob` is universally available in modern browsers and Node.js 16+. If supporting older targets, polyfill or use a proper JWT library like `jose`. |
| **Concurrent tab race condition** | 🟡 Low | `StorageEvent` listener handles cross-tab sync for logout/login. |
| **Token refresh not handled** | 🟡 Low | `refreshUser()` is the hook point; wire it to your token refresh API call. |

